  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "CSS Table Alignment"
    },
    {
      "type": "other",
      "text": "❮ Previous\nNext ❯"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Horizontal Alignment"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The text-align property sets the horizontal alignment (like left, right, or center) \nof the content in <th> or <td>."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "By default, the content of <th> elements are center-aligned and the \ncontent of <td> elements are left-aligned."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "To center-align the content of  <td> elements as well, use text-align: center:"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "data": [
        [
          "Firstname",
          "Lastname",
          "Savings"
        ],
        [
          "Peter",
          "Griffin",
          "$100"
        ],
        [
          "Lois",
          "Griffin",
          "$150"
        ],
        [
          "Joe",
          "Swanson",
          "$300"
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "unknown",
          "code": "td\n{\n   \ntext-align: center;\n}"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "To left-align the content, force the alignment of <th> elements to be \nleft-aligned, with the text-align: left property:"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "data": [
        [
          "Firstname",
          "Lastname",
          "Savings"
        ],
        [
          "Peter",
          "Griffin",
          "$100"
        ],
        [
          "Lois",
          "Griffin",
          "$150"
        ],
        [
          "Joe",
          "Swanson",
          "$300"
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "unknown",
          "code": "th\n{\n   \ntext-align: left;\n}"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Vertical Alignment"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The vertical-align property sets the vertical alignment (like top, bottom, or middle) \nof the content in <th> or <td>."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "By default, the vertical alignment of the content in a table is middle (for both <th> \nand <td> elements)."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The following example sets the vertical text alignment to bottom for <td> elements:"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "data": [
        [
          "Firstname",
          "Lastname",
          "Savings"
        ],
        [
          "Peter",
          "Griffin",
          "$100"
        ],
        [
          "Lois",
          "Griffin",
          "$150"
        ],
        [
          "Joe",
          "Swanson",
          "$300"
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "unknown",
          "code": "td\n{\n   \nheight: 50px;\n   \nvertical-align: bottom;\n}"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
